payload.description: A simulation framework for evaluating adversarial search algorithms in deterministic, turn-based environments. Designed to study decision-making in zero-sum, perfect-information games.

issue.title: `--uuid-from-file -` with empty input, should not operate over *all Photos*
issue.body:
**Is your feature request related to a problem? Please describe.**
Bumped into this issue `cat empty.csv | osxphotos push-exif datetime,location --uuid-from-file - --force` would make timewarp operate over *all* Photos in Library.

**Describe the solution you'd like**
Would like that when an empty uuid file of stdin is provided timewarp should not operate on all Photos.

**Describe alternatives you've considered**
Currently, I'm checking the input or the file size and prevent calling timewarp.

**Additional context**
```
osxphotos --version 
osxphotos, version 0.70.0
Python 3.12.7 (main, Oct 11 2024, 17:54:25) [Clang 14.0.0 (clang-1400.0.29.202)]
Python executable: /Users/MSP/Documents/GitHub/osxphotos/venv/bin/python
macOS 12.7.6, x86_64

```

review.body:
## Pull Request Overview

This PR integrates the backend API consumption by replacing the old Axios configuration with a new WebAPI service. The changes include introducing a new WebAPI class to create an Axios instance, refactoring BaseService to use the new API service, and updating the Home page to interact with this service.
- Added a WebAPI class in src/services/config/WebAPI.js to encapsulate Axios instance creation.
- Removed the old Api.js file in favor of the WebAPI approach.
- Updated BaseService and Home.jsx to utilize the new API service.

### Reviewed Changes

Copilot reviewed 4 out of 4 changed files in this pull request and generated no comments.

| File                              | Description                                           |
| --------------------------------- | ----------------------------------------------------- |
| src/services/config/WebAPI.js     | New class encapsulating Axios instance configuration. |
| src/services/config/Api.js        | Removed obsolete Axios instance file.               |
| src/services/BaseService.js       | Service refactored to use the new WebAPI instance.    |
| src/pages/Home.jsx                | UI updated to call the new API service via BaseService.|


<details>
<summary>Comments suppressed due to low confidence (1)</summary>

**src/services/config/WebAPI.js:7**
* [nitpick] Consider renaming the 'Instance' method to 'instance' to follow standard JavaScript naming conventions for methods.
```
Instance() {
```
</details>
